==English==

===Pronunciation===
\Kom*press"\
*{{audio|en-us-compress-noun.ogg|Audio (US), noun}}
*{{audio|en-us-compress-verb.ogg|Audio (US), verb}}

===Noun===
'''compress'''
# A folded piece of [[cloth]], a [[pouch]] of [[ice]], etc., used to cover the dressing of wounds, and placed with the aid of a [[bandage]] to apply [[pressure]] on an injury.
#:''He held a cold '''compress''' over the sprain.''

===Verb===
'''compress'''
#(''transitive'') To make smaller; to [[press]] or [[squeeze]] together, or to make something occupy a smaller space or volume; to [[condense]] or [[abridge]].
#:''If you try to '''compress''' the entire book into a three-sentence summary, you will lose a lot of information.''
#:''The force required to '''compress''' a spring varies linearly with the displacement.''


